The history of Canadian rock trio Rush, from their early years in Toronto,
through each of their landmark albums and up to the present day. The film
features extensive interviews with all three band members - Geddy Lee, Alex
Lifeson, and Neil Peart - as well as contributions from contemporaries and
admirers including Gene Simmons (Kiss), Billy Corgan (Smashing Pumpkins),
Sebastian Bach (Skid Row), Kirk Hammett (Metallica) and actor Jack Black.
